> Step aside, fussy and overly-expensive lobster rolls! There's a new supreme seafood sandwich in town: warm buttered shrimp rolls. This simple yet indulgent-tasting dish is perfect for busy weeknights, date nights, and everything in between. Sea you at dinner!

== Potato Wedges ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Zest and halve @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lemon and halve both). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, half the @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest of each spice later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Creamy Lemon Slaw ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), half the @celery salt{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), and @sugar{1.5%tsp} (3 tsp for 4). Add @shredded red cabbage{4%ounce} and scallion greens; toss to coat. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set aside.

== Toasted Baguettes ==

Place @butter{1%TBSP} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}.

Slice @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through. Brush melted butter onto cut sides of bread. Place, cut sides up, directly on oven rack (or use a baking sheet); toast until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Shrimp ==

While baguettes toast, rinse @shrimp{10%ounce} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Toss in a second medium bowl with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, remaining paprika, remaining garlic powder, remaining celery salt, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Once pan is hot, add shrimp and scallion whites. Cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are opaque and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%TBSP} and lemon zest to taste.

== Corn on the Cob ==

While shrimp cooks, wrap @corn on the cob{1} in damp paper towels. Microwave until kernels are softened and corn is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes}. Let rest for ~{1%minute}; halve corn crosswise.

== Assembly ==

Fill toasted baguettes with shrimp, as much slaw as you like, and @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired.

Divide shrimp rolls, corn, and potato wedges between plates. Slice remaining lemon into wedges and serve on the side.

> TIP: If you have ketchup on hand, serve some on the side for dipping.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.